#Detection techniques practiced
This lab introduced several detection methods used by SOC analysts to identify suspicious activity on Windows systems.
Key detection areas included:
- Process creation monitoring
  -- Monitoring process creation events to identify suspicious executables, unexpected command line arguments, or
     abnormal parent-child relationships.
- Network connection monitoring
  -- Reviewing network connection events to detect possible command-and-control communication or 
     suspicious outbound connections.
- File and object activity
  -- Detecting file-related activity that may indicate malicious execution or persistent attempts.
- Security event correlation
  -- Correlating multiple event types to understand attacker behavior and reconstruct attack timeline.
